title: Milton Friedman - Free Markets, Free Trade, Medicare, Individual Liberty
description: Economist Milton Friedman discusses various subjects in the context of the free market. Does free trade and free market capitalism deliver to the individual and society the greatest freedom, choice and standard of living? Or does an economic system involving greater government control over the marketplace, means of production, and higher regulation of business achieve a more desireable outcome?
